1
00:00:05,138 --> 00:00:06,511
It must be Petchprakai's karma

2
00:00:06,511 --> 00:00:08,400
that everyone we groom ends up betraying us.

3
00:00:09,166 --> 00:00:11,709
Our job is to bring people joy.

4
00:00:11,709 --> 00:00:13,866
So why shouldn't we bring some to ourselves?

5
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:15,866
Don't ever leave Petchprakai, Ploy.

6
00:00:16,566 --> 00:00:18,400
I promise.

7
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:22,794
You are the one chosen as the most suitable.

8
00:00:22,794 --> 00:00:24,636
I want you to respect yourself

9
00:00:24,636 --> 00:00:26,766
and respect the team's decision as well.

10
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:28,800
Can I leave my brother with you?

11
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,766
I'll take the best care of Guy.

12
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:35,166
I won't tire of your brother for a single second.

13
00:00:41,317 --> 00:00:45,239
(Tor Prakai's Instagram Page)

14
00:01:03,966 --> 00:01:07,500
If you stalk him this much, just follow him.

15
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:10,966
I'm not looking at anything.

16
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:12,500
Mmm.

17
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:16,866
It was just a suggestion, so I clicked it.

18
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:21,666
I'm just looking.

19
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,600
Guy is going to be a star.

20
00:01:28,133 --> 00:01:30,333
He'd definitely want more followers, don't you think?

21
00:01:31,366 --> 00:01:32,900
You should follow him.

22
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,366
Think of it as helping him out.

23
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:39,166
You’re really not gonna talk to him?

24
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,600
What do you want me to say?

25
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:45,600
I don't see Guy wanting to talk to me either.

26
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,472
You should message him first.

27
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:50,635
He’s your brother, for heaven’s sake.

28
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:53,799
You're so capable with everything else.

29
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,800
Just press it.

30
00:02:01,085 --> 00:02:02,509
(Tor Prakai's Instagram Page)

31
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:08,566
I'm pressing it.

32
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:10,700
Just like that.

33
00:03:57,866 --> 00:03:59,533
Hello, Boss Ah.

34
00:04:04,778 --> 00:04:05,278
Boss is here.

35
00:04:05,278 --> 00:04:06,112
This damn guy.

36
00:04:06,112 --> 00:04:06,612
Forgot your roots?

37
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:14,700
Show off a bit, you rich man.

38
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:26,844
Want some?

39
00:04:26,844 --> 00:04:27,666
No.

40
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,374
I'm asking...

41
00:04:36,002 --> 00:04:38,195
I'm so sorry.

42
00:04:39,721 --> 00:04:41,173
You're probably wondering, right?

43
00:04:41,173 --> 00:04:42,375
Why I

44
00:04:42,375 --> 00:04:42,949
am here?

45
00:04:43,557 --> 00:04:44,057
Yes.

46
00:04:44,725 --> 00:04:47,130
Because I've been paying my debt

47
00:04:47,654 --> 00:04:48,978
to you on time every month.

48
00:04:49,169 --> 00:04:50,146
True.

49
00:04:50,861 --> 00:04:51,713
Correct.

50
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,879
My dear nephew.

51
00:04:53,879 --> 00:04:55,750
Sending money to me

52
00:04:55,750 --> 00:04:56,414
is great.

53
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,596
I see you

54
00:04:58,596 --> 00:05:01,388
taking such good care of the Likay troupe.

55
00:05:01,388 --> 00:05:03,126
So I thought

56
00:05:03,508 --> 00:05:04,978
you'd have the money to pay me back

57
00:05:05,646 --> 00:05:07,110
much faster, right?

58
00:05:12,466 --> 00:05:15,003
So I'd like to ask

59
00:05:17,244 --> 00:05:20,200
to increase the payment to 200,000 a month.

60
00:05:21,266 --> 00:05:22,066
Oh.

61
00:05:22,566 --> 00:05:24,300
Isn't this illegal, Boss?

62
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,333
I still have the old contract.

63
00:05:26,866 --> 00:05:28,642
I can report this to the police.

64
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:30,933
Why do you sound so scary?

65
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:32,733
Who would it be?

66
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:33,700
Which police officer

67
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:34,900
would take the report?

68
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,266
No one dares.

69
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,600
Oh.

70
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,300
Mmm.

71
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,818
Boss,

72
00:05:44,818 --> 00:05:46,103
I'm short on cash.

73
00:05:46,675 --> 00:05:47,609
Out of money.

74
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:49,037
Too many girls.

75
00:05:49,561 --> 00:05:50,633
Raising young girls.

76
00:05:50,824 --> 00:05:51,815
Too many mistresses.

77
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,915
Being handsome makes me a philanderer.

78
00:05:55,675 --> 00:05:58,533
It shouldn't be a problem, right, nephew?

79
00:05:59,773 --> 00:06:01,678
So I'd like to ask

80
00:06:01,678 --> 00:06:03,763
for the next installment first.

81
00:06:03,763 --> 00:06:05,073
Can you do that, nephew Phet?

82
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:12,125
I can, Boss.

83
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,013
I'll

84
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:15,828
look into it.

85
00:06:15,828 --> 00:06:16,541
Wow.

86
00:06:17,542 --> 00:06:18,732
Wow.

87
00:06:19,447 --> 00:06:22,305
You're so sweet, nephew Phet.

88
00:06:22,305 --> 00:06:24,137
Can I have a kiss?

89
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:28,157
Just what I wanted.

90
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,311
Got the money.

91
00:06:33,311 --> 00:06:34,097
Let's go back.

92
00:06:34,097 --> 00:06:34,879
Go back.

93
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,842
P'Phet.

94
00:06:43,842 --> 00:06:45,830
That Boss Ah is cheating us.

95
00:06:46,688 --> 00:06:47,990
Why do we have to give in to him?

96
00:06:49,866 --> 00:06:51,091
I'm the debtor anyway.

97
00:06:51,949 --> 00:06:54,311
And it's my duty to pay it back.

98
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:55,492
Look at it this way,

99
00:06:56,255 --> 00:06:57,819
the debt will be cleared sooner.

100
00:06:58,533 --> 00:07:00,281
But it's 200,000 a month.

101
00:07:00,662 --> 00:07:02,281
Are you sure you can handle that?

102
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,282
Soon,

103
00:07:09,616 --> 00:07:12,368
I'll plan our gigs better next month.

104
00:07:12,988 --> 00:07:14,325
As for this month,

105
00:07:28,266 --> 00:07:31,400
I'll pawn whatever I can for now.

106
00:07:32,566 --> 00:07:34,819
But those are our parents' inheritance.

107
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,013
Are you really going to let them go?

108
00:07:40,566 --> 00:07:42,540
I'm just leaving them with Boss.

109
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:45,881
Once I have the money, I'll get them back.

110
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:48,600
And how can you trust someone like Boss Ah?

111
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:18,378
This money...

112
00:08:19,189 --> 00:08:21,631
I intended to use it to cancel the series contract.

113
00:08:22,599 --> 00:08:24,914
But I don't need it anymore. You take it.

114
00:08:27,066 --> 00:08:28,237
I can't, Ploy.

115
00:08:29,668 --> 00:08:31,048
It's my problem.

116
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:37,332
How can you say that?

117
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:40,355
Your problem is my problem.

118
00:08:41,929 --> 00:08:43,464
If there's anything I can do to help,

119
00:08:43,464 --> 00:08:45,051
please just let me.

120
00:08:45,432 --> 00:08:45,957
This money...

121
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,256
I intended to keep it as a Petchprakai fund.

122
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,462
I'm happy

123
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:58,229
that I get to use it in an emergency.

124
00:09:06,566 --> 00:09:08,102
Thank you, Ploy.

125
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:37,733
Thank you.

126
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:41,600
We'll get through this together.

127
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:21,800
Hey.

128
00:10:22,366 --> 00:10:23,300
Are you okay?

129
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,600
What were you talking to my brother about?

130
00:10:28,966 --> 00:10:29,766
It's a secret.

131
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:33,366
How can my family's business be a secret?

132
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,800
Well,

133
00:10:35,366 --> 00:10:37,166
if it's about your family,

134
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,166
then why don't you ask him?

135
00:10:45,937 --> 00:10:48,375
It's nothing.

136
00:10:49,281 --> 00:10:51,693
Your brother just asked me to look after you.

137
00:10:53,315 --> 00:10:55,326
He's very worried about you.

138
00:10:57,281 --> 00:10:58,634
So am I.

139
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,200
Why worry?

140
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,266
There's nothing going on.

141
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:16,100
Hmm?

142
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:18,100
Look how stubborn you are.

143
00:11:21,933 --> 00:11:23,100
You're a famous star.

144
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,866
You must have plenty of friends.

145
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:26,592
But why

146
00:11:27,355 --> 00:11:28,566
do you have to keep looking after me?

147
00:11:28,866 --> 00:11:29,771
I'm charitable, I guess.

148
00:11:29,771 --> 00:11:30,271
Oh?

149
00:11:32,566 --> 00:11:34,100
It's strange.

150
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,266
When I see you, it reminds me of

151
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,266
a little dog.

152
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,366
One that barks a lot

153
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,133
but doesn't bite hard.

154
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,700
And when I play with it...

155
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:44,933
hmm...

156
00:11:45,166 --> 00:11:46,166
it's got so much fight in it.

157
00:11:49,133 --> 00:11:51,066
Are you calling me a dog?

158
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:53,000
But I like dogs.

159
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,733
They're straightforward and not complicated.

160
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,866
I feel at ease when I'm with them.

161
00:12:00,366 --> 00:12:02,200
I've never been this attached before.

162
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,466
It might not be as good as you think.

163
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:12,266
Anything I like

164
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,000
is always good.

165
00:12:32,066 --> 00:12:32,631
Hey.

166
00:12:34,157 --> 00:12:34,848
There are cameras.

167
00:12:41,066 --> 00:12:41,711
Okay.

168
00:12:41,997 --> 00:12:44,752
Get some rest then. See you tomorrow.

169
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,000
I forgot to mention...

170
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,769
I like dogs too.

171
00:13:11,915 --> 00:13:12,703
Especially

172
00:13:13,847 --> 00:13:15,227
big dogs

173
00:13:15,942 --> 00:13:17,333
with big mouths

174
00:13:18,191 --> 00:13:19,495
but kind hearts.

175
00:13:33,366 --> 00:13:34,500
See you tomorrow.

176
00:14:02,066 --> 00:14:05,066
Still wearing your uniform for summer school?

177
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:09,366
"Well, I look good in it. Once I graduate,
I won't get to wear it anymore."

178
00:14:10,133 --> 00:14:14,033
Right, you still have one year left.

179
00:14:14,033 --> 00:14:16,566
You might as well wear it to bed then.

180
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,000
Okay.

181
00:14:19,966 --> 00:14:25,200
Hey, do you think the freshmen will be as hot as our year?

182
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:28,806
You're a junior now.

183
00:14:28,806 --> 00:14:30,795
Still interested in freshmen?

184
00:14:30,795 --> 00:14:32,366
They're going to call you "Auntie."

185
00:14:32,766 --> 00:14:34,410
Bring it on.

186
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:36,696
Such a puppy.

187
00:14:36,696 --> 00:14:39,166
This big sis will spoil you myself.

188
00:14:42,966 --> 00:14:44,510
Whoa.

189
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:47,490
This is totally my type.

190
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:51,766
A lowlife-styled puppy boy with a loud exhaust.

191
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:01,566
Lynchee.

192
00:15:04,133 --> 00:15:04,933
Hey.

193
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,700
Do you even know what a "puppy boy" is?

194
00:15:08,166 --> 00:15:11,100
See? I've enrolled. Do I look like I have a future now?

195
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:14,100
To have a future, you have to graduate first.

196
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:17,604
But you haven't graduated either.

197
00:15:17,604 --> 00:15:19,100
So you don't have a future yet either.

198
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:22,533
I'll definitely graduate. You just finish your first term.

199
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:24,533
Mmm, I'll definitely survive.

200
00:15:25,866 --> 00:15:28,366
By the way, what do I get if I graduate?

201
00:15:28,566 --> 00:15:30,555
You get to study in the second term.

202
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:32,600
Stop asking weird stuff and just go.

203
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:33,566
Hey, wait.

204
00:15:34,366 --> 00:15:37,066
I just got here. Is this all the time we get?

205
00:15:37,966 --> 00:15:40,064
I'm a student, not a faculty sign.

206
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,733
You expect me to stay all day and night?
School's out, I'm going home.

207
00:15:43,566 --> 00:15:44,573
Let's go.

208
00:15:44,573 --> 00:15:45,707
Wait.

209
00:15:45,707 --> 00:15:46,207
And...

210
00:15:46,207 --> 00:15:47,400
how are you getting back?

211
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:49,333
Calling a ride.

212
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,340
Here it is.

213
00:15:52,816 --> 00:15:53,316
The car.

214
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:55,000
The driver.

215
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:59,200
And are you going to get us lost again?

216
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,093
I don't know about getting lost on the road,

217
00:16:01,093 --> 00:16:03,666
but I'm already lost in you.

218
00:16:04,166 --> 00:16:06,733
Ooh, puppy boy.

219
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:08,195
Please.

220
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:11,800
Guaranteed five-star safe ride, ma'am.

221
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:13,700
Let's go.

222
00:16:17,166 --> 00:16:17,966
I'm off.

223
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:23,466
One, two, three.

224
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:40,474
Here, let me help.

225
00:16:40,474 --> 00:16:41,182
It's okay.

226
00:16:41,182 --> 00:16:41,733
Grandma.

227
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:42,933
Let me help.

228
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,133
All done.

229
00:16:48,733 --> 00:16:49,666
Grandma's going to give you a reward.

230
00:16:51,366 --> 00:16:52,333
Looks delicious.

231
00:16:53,383 --> 00:16:54,214
Thank you very much.

232
00:16:56,666 --> 00:16:57,365
Bananas.

233
00:16:57,365 --> 00:16:59,200
One, two, three, heave!

234
00:17:00,066 --> 00:17:00,866
Straight ahead.

235
00:17:34,566 --> 00:17:35,125
Hey, hey, hey!

236
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:35,789
Aie!

237
00:17:35,789 --> 00:17:37,720
Hey, hey, hey!

238
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:38,693
Hey, what's wrong with the bike?

239
00:17:41,945 --> 00:17:43,099
I don't know.

240
00:17:43,099 --> 00:17:44,269
It was fine just a second ago.

241
00:17:45,461 --> 00:17:46,367
What the hell's wrong?

242
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:47,739
Oh! I forgot the kickstand.

243
00:17:54,466 --> 00:17:55,445
Mmm.

244
00:17:56,971 --> 00:17:57,811
Seriously though,

245
00:17:58,717 --> 00:18:00,581
are you serious about studying?

246
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:02,856
Mmm-hmm.

247
00:18:03,619 --> 00:18:04,426
For real?

248
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:05,405
Why?

249
00:18:06,566 --> 00:18:08,191
Don't tell me...

250
00:18:08,191 --> 00:18:09,066
it's because of me.

251
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:11,733
Hey.

252
00:18:13,866 --> 00:18:14,666
What's that smell?

253
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:15,933
What smell?

254
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,000
I don't smell anything.

255
00:18:17,766 --> 00:18:18,566
Right here.

256
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,000
The smell of narcissism.

257
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,000
I was asking nicely.

258
00:18:24,528 --> 00:18:25,251
Well...

259
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:26,924
because of you, maybe...

260
00:18:27,735 --> 00:18:28,700
about 50 percent.

261
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,500
Hmm?

262
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,900
And the other 50?

263
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:33,526
Didn't you say it yourself?

264
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,966
That nobody likes to struggle.

265
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:38,300
I don't like it either.

266
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:40,670
I just...

267
00:18:41,528 --> 00:18:43,300
want to make my future better.

268
00:18:44,366 --> 00:18:45,266
I'll be comfortable,

269
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,300
and Ploy will be comfortable too.

270
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:49,966
And most importantly,

271
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,333
you won't get scolded by your dad

272
00:18:53,866 --> 00:18:55,300
for dating a loser.

273
00:18:56,866 --> 00:18:57,666
That was almost good.

274
00:18:58,133 --> 00:18:59,400
When did I say I'd date you?

275
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:00,700
You don't have to say it.

276
00:19:01,366 --> 00:19:03,100
Just by looking into your eyes,

277
00:19:05,533 --> 00:19:06,333
I can tell

278
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:07,800
that you're...

279
00:19:07,966 --> 00:19:09,100
my future girlfriend.

280
00:19:10,566 --> 00:19:11,400
Do you smell something?

281
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:12,900
Don't tell me.

282
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:13,800
Don't tell me.

283
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:14,966
The smell of narcissism...

284
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:16,062
is so strong right here.

285
00:19:16,062 --> 00:19:16,666
Hmm.

286
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:18,500
Just my style.

287
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:19,400
Exactly my style.

288
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:20,766
A sassy girl like you.

289
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,411
Mmm, I'll give you...

290
00:19:25,411 --> 00:19:26,917
10 points for now.

291
00:19:26,917 --> 00:19:28,855
Because you enrolled,

292
00:19:28,855 --> 00:19:31,900
and another 10 because you didn't get lost.

293
00:19:32,066 --> 00:19:32,866
What points?

294
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,927
If you collect 100 points,

295
00:19:34,927 --> 00:19:36,100
then we'll be boyfriend and girlfriend.

296
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,300
Hey, for real?

297
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,666
But Professor Lynchee doesn't give easy grades.

298
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,966
If student Pleng Chai is slow to score,

299
00:19:46,366 --> 00:19:47,166
then...

300
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:51,713
the professor will flirt with you instead.

301
00:19:51,713 --> 00:19:52,333
Oops.

302
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:55,900
Then I'll be slow; I want to be flirted with.

303
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:57,333
I forgot to tell you.

304
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,733
This is my house.

305
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,066
I'll have Daddy's men help fix it.

306
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:01,700
I'm off.

307
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:02,500
Bye-bye.

308
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:05,466
Bye-bye.

309
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:09,966
Hey, give it back!

310
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,336
Hey, hey, hey!

311
00:20:15,053 --> 00:20:16,200
That's a lot.

312
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:18,103
Ping Pong.

313
00:20:18,103 --> 00:20:20,959
Why tease him? He'll really get mad.

314
00:20:20,959 --> 00:20:22,066
Eat properly.

315
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:33,366
It's here!

316
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:35,533
Heave!

317
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:37,066
Riding together on a bike like that...

318
00:20:37,366 --> 00:20:38,400
what's the deal between you two?

319
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:50,900
You guys just love to tease.

320
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:54,400
I'm just hungry.

321
00:20:54,866 --> 00:20:56,500
Someone said the porridge here is delicious.

322
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:58,266
If it's not good,

323
00:20:58,933 --> 00:20:59,966
points will definitely be deducted.

324
00:21:00,666 --> 00:21:01,766
And if it's delicious,

325
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,400
do I get to be your boyfriend?

326
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:07,864
(Lynchee) In your dreams.
(Pleng Chai) Hey!

327
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:09,800
What the hell?

328
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:13,258
Good that Lynchee is here.

329
00:21:13,258 --> 00:21:14,545
Actually,

330
00:21:14,545 --> 00:21:16,733
we have something we need help with.

331
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,837
From next month onwards,

332
00:21:20,552 --> 00:21:22,534
our troupe has to pay off Boss Ah's debt

333
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:24,466
at 200,000 baht a month.

334
00:21:24,766 --> 00:21:25,566
200,000?

335
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,750
I've done the math, adding up everyone's fees

336
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,815
and other expenses for the troupe,

337
00:21:36,815 --> 00:21:38,820
we need to make

338
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,697
no less than 300,000 baht a month.

339
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:48,700
I've called every customer lately,

340
00:21:49,966 --> 00:21:52,900
but no one wants to book a Likay gig.

341
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,066
Then we have to take more frequent gigs.

342
00:21:56,666 --> 00:21:58,028
But it's unpredictable.

343
00:21:58,457 --> 00:22:00,041
Some days there are many viewers,

344
00:22:00,327 --> 00:22:02,052
some days there are few.

345
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:06,466
"Oh, and for the livestreams,
where does everyone promote them?"

346
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,819
Here, let me show you.

347
00:22:15,394 --> 00:22:20,501
We post on the page and write that

348
00:22:20,501 --> 00:22:22,066
we'll be live from this time to that time.

349
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,160
I suggest

350
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:35,400
Petchprakai should try adjusting the promotion.

351
00:22:36,666 --> 00:22:41,666
"I've made a new poster in Gen Z style:
(Watch for Free: Vertical Likay, the First in Thailand)."

352
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:43,099
It's quite chic.

353
00:22:43,099 --> 00:22:43,599
But...

354
00:22:44,666 --> 00:22:46,266
my face looks fat in this photo.

355
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:47,500
What should I do?

356
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,866
No problem, P'Ploy.

357
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,366
I'll edit it for you.

358
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:53,133
Vertical Likay.

359
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:55,483
I adapted it from the term

360
00:22:55,483 --> 00:22:58,133
vertical series' that people like to watch nowadays.

361
00:22:58,866 --> 00:23:02,400
I think if we promote it as 'Vertical Likay,'

362
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:05,566
it will definitely be much more interesting.

363
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:08,766
But importantly, we can't just post it.

364
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:12,166
We have to run ads too.

365
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:15,266
"To increase visibility so more people can see it:
(Watch for Free: Vertical Likay, the First in Thailand)."

366
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,400
Hello.

367
00:23:16,666 --> 00:23:18,966
We are now here with the Petchprakai Troupe.

368
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,900
And what story are we doing today?

369
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,600
Janthakorop.

370
00:23:22,966 --> 00:23:26,488
The Master has sacred charms for his disciples

371
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:27,966
to carry by their sides.

372
00:23:28,733 --> 00:23:30,500
You cannot eat it, child. Spit it out first.

373
00:23:31,500 --> 00:23:32,800
I think it's interesting.

374
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:35,366
We can try opening up new markets.

375
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:38,566
Will the new generation be interested in Likay?

376
00:23:38,700 --> 00:23:40,300
One day with the Likay troupe.

377
00:23:40,466 --> 00:23:41,733
We start with the right side first.

378
00:23:42,066 --> 00:23:43,400
Right, left, right.

379
00:23:44,866 --> 00:23:47,178
I think if the content we make

380
00:23:47,178 --> 00:23:50,733
is good, has a story, and fits current trends,

381
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:53,466
the new generation will definitely come to watch.

382
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,764
The final four contestants

383
00:23:55,764 --> 00:23:58,566
want to create this dish for me.

384
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,733
Today, I am serving...

385
00:23:59,733 --> 00:24:02,951
-@&;฿372/@-

386
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,000
One more time, please.

387
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,455
-@&;฿372/@-

388
00:24:06,971 --> 00:24:08,202
Who's chanting?

389
00:24:09,012 --> 00:24:11,710
Nobita, you're in trouble.

390
00:24:26,466 --> 00:24:30,620
Remember, child, don't open this casket on the way.

391
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:31,692
Why, Your Majesty?

392
00:24:31,692 --> 00:24:33,120
Because you might get hit by a car, child.

393
00:24:34,407 --> 00:24:35,908
So this is Naphanapha?

394
00:24:35,908 --> 00:24:37,982
Nok is on P'Ta's side.

395
00:24:38,458 --> 00:24:39,160
Transform!

396
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,492
Oh, it's all spilled, sir.

397
00:24:41,017 --> 00:24:41,517
Hyee!

398
00:24:41,517 --> 00:24:42,392
"(Ploy Ying) Not yet…
(Phet Thae) ...haven't eaten yet."

399
00:24:42,392 --> 00:24:43,130
♪ Bua Loy ♪

400
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:50,000
♪ This dish shall capture your heart ♪

401
00:24:51,766 --> 00:24:53,866
Push the palanquin, I'm going to slap her!

402
00:24:54,533 --> 00:24:55,366
I'm going to slap her!

403
00:24:58,133 --> 00:24:59,766
♪ For today, the time has come to an end ♪

404
00:25:01,483 --> 00:25:03,724
♪ Until the next chance arises ♪

405
00:25:05,441 --> 00:25:07,433
♪ We meet again ♪

406
00:25:12,733 --> 00:25:14,600
Whoa, TikTok is blowing up!

407
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,333
Hey, what are you guys watching?

408
00:25:16,866 --> 00:25:17,666
P'Ploy.

409
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:18,666
TikTok?

410
00:25:18,666 --> 00:25:19,466
Look at this.

411
00:25:19,666 --> 00:25:20,187
What?

412
00:25:20,187 --> 00:25:21,100
"Look at the numbers.(250K followers)"

413
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:22,500
Whoa.

414
00:25:23,466 --> 00:25:26,366
And how much money have we made now?

415
00:25:26,666 --> 00:25:28,300
Uh, hold on a second, let me check.

416
00:25:29,533 --> 00:25:30,333
Whoa.

417
00:25:31,766 --> 00:25:32,566
Whoa.

418
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,100
Yeah.

419
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:35,700
We're still 220,000 short.

420
00:25:36,566 --> 00:25:37,333
Still a lot.

421
00:25:37,333 --> 00:25:39,158
P'Ploy, calm down.

422
00:25:39,158 --> 00:25:40,866
We've only just started.

423
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:41,500
True.

424
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,269
But I think you don't have to worry.

425
00:25:43,269 --> 00:25:46,700
Should we try adding a business model?

426
00:25:47,066 --> 00:25:48,733
Mmm, like adding a shopping cart?

427
00:25:48,933 --> 00:25:49,638
Yeah.

428
00:25:49,638 --> 00:25:51,600
Or taking on product reviews.

429
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:53,900
Trust me.

430
00:25:54,266 --> 00:25:55,066
That's interesting.

431
00:25:55,066 --> 00:25:55,969
Hey, who's messaging?

432
00:25:55,969 --> 00:25:56,500
What is it?

433
00:25:57,920 --> 00:25:58,737
Hello.

434
00:25:58,737 --> 00:26:00,000
Does the Petchprakai Troupe take product reviews?

435
00:26:01,366 --> 00:26:02,600
Send the rate card immediately!

436
00:26:02,766 --> 00:26:03,566
Send the rate card!

437
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:04,900
The rate card...

438
00:26:06,466 --> 00:26:07,500
...the channel's fee.

439
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:09,733
Yeah, that's it!

440
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:10,800
Sent!

441
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:11,979
(Rate Card)

442
00:26:12,766 --> 00:26:14,266
I hope more come in.

443
00:26:14,966 --> 00:26:16,133
"Hey, another one!
(Hello, I'm interested in a product review.)"

444
00:26:16,266 --> 00:26:16,800
Another one.

445
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,866
(Lynchee) Send it fast, don't just talk.
(Ploy Ying) Do it now!

446
00:26:18,866 --> 00:26:20,233
Are there any jobs for us?

447
00:26:20,233 --> 00:26:20,733
Yeah.

448
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:22,200
Here.

449
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,800
This looks suitable for you guys.

450
00:26:24,166 --> 00:26:25,000
"Let me see your legs.
(Hair removal cream)"

451
00:26:27,666 --> 00:26:29,100
You guys handle the shoot, okay?

452
00:26:29,366 --> 00:26:30,166
Sure!

453
00:26:30,466 --> 00:26:32,166
"This one is definitely for you.
(Ab-burning exercise machine)"

454
00:26:32,666 --> 00:26:33,218
Very clear.

455
00:26:33,218 --> 00:26:34,529
Totally you.

456
00:26:34,529 --> 00:26:35,029
I'll take it.

457
00:26:35,866 --> 00:26:36,366
Hey.

458
00:26:36,366 --> 00:26:36,866
What?

459
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:37,900
What?

460
00:26:37,966 --> 00:26:38,466
I'll take it myself.

461
00:26:38,466 --> 00:26:39,100
I'll take this one myself.

462
00:26:39,266 --> 00:26:40,816
(Pong) What is it?
(Lynchee) I was trying not to say anything.

463
00:26:40,816 --> 00:26:41,566
Hey, don't butt in.

464
00:26:42,233 --> 00:26:44,121
♪ When the beloved disciple ♪

465
00:26:44,121 --> 00:26:46,121
♪ comes to bid farewell ♪

466
00:26:46,475 --> 00:26:48,832
♪ comes to bid farewell ♪

467
00:26:48,832 --> 00:26:50,864
♪ to the Hermit Grandfather ♪

468
00:26:51,293 --> 00:26:53,933
♪ may you be safely on your way ♪

469
00:26:53,933 --> 00:26:56,066
Finish the shoot first instead of changing?

470
00:26:56,500 --> 00:26:58,333
Gosh, let me rest a bit.

471
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:01,666
Hey, you.

472
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:02,800
Hmm?

473
00:27:02,866 --> 00:27:04,966
Do you think people will like our pilot?

474
00:27:05,900 --> 00:27:06,973
They will.

475
00:27:06,973 --> 00:27:07,700
How do you know?

476
00:27:08,166 --> 00:27:09,975
Well, I'm a person too.

477
00:27:10,643 --> 00:27:11,943
I should be able to tell, right?

478
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:17,266
"I don't mean just anyone, but the fans…
...or the novel fans."

479
00:27:20,066 --> 00:27:21,474
I don't know.

480
00:27:21,474 --> 00:27:22,802
But we both gave it our all.

481
00:27:22,802 --> 00:27:23,909
We did our best.

482
00:27:24,386 --> 00:27:25,431
Now, we just have to...

483
00:27:25,860 --> 00:27:26,841
...wait and see together.

484
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:28,580
Right?

485
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:36,733
Your brother's Likay?

486
00:27:37,247 --> 00:27:38,047
Mmm-hmm.

487
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:40,400
They've been streaming almost every day lately.

488
00:27:41,533 --> 00:27:43,900
No wonder you look sleepy.

489
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:45,400
Hey.

490
00:27:45,925 --> 00:27:47,362
I'm not complaining or anything.

491
00:27:48,125 --> 00:27:49,174
I'm just worried.

492
00:27:49,699 --> 00:27:51,694
We've both been working hard lately.

493
00:27:52,266 --> 00:27:53,885
I want you to get some rest.

494
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:56,100
I am resting.

495
00:27:57,933 --> 00:27:59,266
Just watching a bit before bed.

496
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:05,166
And how much longer are you staying at that hotel?

497
00:28:06,133 --> 00:28:08,566
All the money you earn goes to hotel bills.

498
00:28:08,866 --> 00:28:10,533
I don't think you can keep this up.

499
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,466
I'm looking for a dorm.

500
00:28:13,966 --> 00:28:15,200
And will it be safe?

501
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:18,700
I don't have money to buy a house like you.

502
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:21,766
In that case,

503
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,066
why don't you live with me?

504
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:25,500
Huh?

505
00:28:25,766 --> 00:28:26,933
My house is spacious.

506
00:28:27,733 --> 00:28:28,666
You can stay with me.

507
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:32,166
Are you trying to lure me?

508
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:35,333
Free water and electricity.

509
00:28:36,266 --> 00:28:37,800
The fridge is full of food.

510
00:28:43,700 --> 00:28:44,700
Let me think about it.

511
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:47,380
Wherever you want to go,

512
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:48,492
there's a shuttle service.

513
00:28:49,255 --> 00:28:52,295
Plus, you'll have someone to watch lives with at night.

514
00:28:53,058 --> 00:28:53,614
Just as friends?

515
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:57,809
Or...

516
00:28:58,286 --> 00:28:59,462
...do you want it to be more?

517
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:14,614
That's enough.

518
00:29:15,758 --> 00:29:16,839
Don't let me stay for free.

519
00:29:17,268 --> 00:29:19,209
Let me help with the bills,

520
00:29:19,209 --> 00:29:21,313
and I'll look after the house in return.

521
00:29:22,457 --> 00:29:23,601
Either way is fine.

522
00:29:23,601 --> 00:29:25,541
I just need you to say yes.

523
00:29:26,662 --> 00:29:28,000
Because I'm lonely.

524
00:29:28,566 --> 00:29:30,066
Aren't you lonely living alone?

525
00:29:31,366 --> 00:29:33,566
Two lonely people living together...

526
00:29:34,733 --> 00:29:35,966
...is a perfect match.

527
00:29:37,266 --> 00:29:38,066
Deal?

528
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:40,100
Deal.

529
00:29:44,133 --> 00:29:44,933
Deal.

530
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:48,300
You said it.

531
00:29:49,333 --> 00:29:50,133
Yeah.

532
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,000
Nine.

533
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,266
To the set, please.

534
00:30:00,566 --> 00:30:03,479
Nong Ning looks so cute.

535
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,596
Come and get it, hot porridge!

536
00:30:09,596 --> 00:30:10,631
Got it.

537
00:30:10,631 --> 00:30:11,666
Give it a try.

538
00:30:14,733 --> 00:30:16,133
How is it? Is it good?

539
00:30:17,133 --> 00:30:19,637
It's delicious. Sweet porridge.

540
00:30:21,366 --> 00:30:24,666
It's sweet because I spilled the sugar.

541
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,600
I thought so.

542
00:30:33,366 --> 00:30:34,654
Babe.

543
00:30:34,654 --> 00:30:35,975
Open your mouth.

544
00:30:35,975 --> 00:30:36,866
I'll feed you.

545
00:30:37,766 --> 00:30:38,566
Ahhh.

546
00:30:40,266 --> 00:30:41,066
Oops.

547
00:30:41,966 --> 00:30:43,766
Tell that "dog" in your mouth...

548
00:30:44,100 --> 00:30:44,900
...to step aside for a bit.

549
00:30:45,133 --> 00:30:46,100
I can't feed you.

550
00:30:47,666 --> 00:30:50,266
Why did you eat so messily?

551
00:30:50,466 --> 00:30:51,900
How did you get it all over like this?

552
00:30:55,166 --> 00:30:57,502
Phet, if you're going to date Ploy,

553
00:30:57,502 --> 00:30:59,333
have you passed my test yet?

554
00:31:00,266 --> 00:31:01,066
What test?

555
00:31:01,066 --> 00:31:03,228
Well, you have to ask for my permission first.

556
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:05,700
Because I am Ploy's guardian.

557
00:31:06,533 --> 00:31:07,557
Since when?

558
00:31:07,557 --> 00:31:10,366
I'm the one who's your guardian.

559
00:31:11,966 --> 00:31:13,700
Then let me ask you something first.

560
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:14,700
Go ahead.

561
00:31:15,333 --> 00:31:17,907
I want to know our livestream income...

562
00:31:17,907 --> 00:31:19,466
...at the moment.

563
00:31:22,733 --> 00:31:23,595
Right now...

564
00:31:24,596 --> 00:31:26,538
...it's not even 200,000 yet.

565
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:36,548
Livestreaming is good,

566
00:31:37,073 --> 00:31:39,700
but I think we need hire-out gigs too.

567
00:31:40,733 --> 00:31:44,066
I'll try calling some old hosts then.

568
00:31:48,333 --> 00:31:48,900
Hey!

569
00:31:48,900 --> 00:31:51,133
"Did you set a notification for Guy's series?
(Teaser: Engineering Mess, On Air Now)"

570
00:31:51,333 --> 00:31:51,833
Yeah.

571
00:31:51,833 --> 00:31:52,333
Hey!

572
00:31:53,666 --> 00:31:54,176
Look.

573
00:31:54,176 --> 00:31:55,866
No, I didn't set it.

574
00:31:55,933 --> 00:31:57,000
Someone misses him!

575
00:31:57,366 --> 00:31:58,533
I didn't set it, Ploy.

576
00:31:58,700 --> 00:32:00,266
It's right there, I can see it.

577
00:32:00,366 --> 00:32:03,066
I don't know why it notified me. I didn't set it.

578
00:32:03,133 --> 00:32:04,400
You watch it a lot, so it popped up.

579
00:32:04,766 --> 00:32:06,066
I didn't set it, I don't know.

580
00:32:06,166 --> 00:32:08,624
Stop arguing for a second. Can we watch it now?

581
00:32:08,624 --> 00:32:09,266
I want to see it.

582
00:32:10,399 --> 00:32:11,533
Just play it.

583
00:32:26,700 --> 00:32:28,200
Guy, Guy, Guy!

584
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:39,366
This lead actor isn't even that handsome.

585
00:32:39,933 --> 00:32:42,566
Sure, no one's as handsome as your "dad."

586
00:32:42,766 --> 00:32:45,566
Hey, we have the same "dad," don't forget.

587
00:32:47,133 --> 00:32:49,169
You want me to pretend to be your boyfriend?

588
00:32:49,169 --> 00:32:53,727
I know I'm small with fair skin and red lips.

589
00:32:54,299 --> 00:32:55,784
But why does it have to be me?

590
00:32:57,119 --> 00:32:58,148
It could've been anyone else.

591
00:33:04,100 --> 00:33:05,166
I want to have So.

592
00:33:07,566 --> 00:33:09,366
Why does the hero want a chain?

593
00:33:09,666 --> 00:33:11,149
Is he going to ride a bike?

594
00:33:11,149 --> 00:33:11,649
Ouch!

595
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:13,400
Ouch!

596
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,500
And does So want to have me?

597
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,630
Whoa!

598
00:33:57,630 --> 00:33:59,131
Here we go!

599
00:34:03,232 --> 00:34:04,352
Guy is so handsome.

600
00:34:04,352 --> 00:34:05,446
Right?

601
00:34:05,446 --> 00:34:06,254
This is so "fin."

602
00:34:06,254 --> 00:34:08,500
I'm sure the audience will love it.

603
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:10,466
But I don't think that kind of scene is necessary.

604
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,370
Scenes like this are exactly what they want.

605
00:34:14,370 --> 00:34:16,638
The fans live for these "fin" moments.

606
00:34:16,638 --> 00:34:19,800
Let's call Guy and tease him about being lovey-dovey.

607
00:34:20,733 --> 00:34:23,700
If you don't believe me, try reading the comments.

608
00:34:24,066 --> 00:34:24,866
Take a look.

609
00:34:34,402 --> 00:34:36,067
This cast totally disrespects the original novel.

610
00:34:36,067 --> 00:34:36,740
I don't want to watch because of the "Uke."

611
00:34:36,740 --> 00:34:38,252
Why isn't P'Toey playing this role?

612
00:34:38,252 --> 00:34:38,752
Toey is a million times more suitable.

613
00:34:38,752 --> 00:34:40,378
Nine-Toey only.

614
00:34:40,378 --> 00:34:41,450
Why isn't P'Toey playing this role?

615
00:34:41,450 --> 00:34:42,938
This cast totally disrespects the original novel.

616
00:34:42,938 --> 00:34:44,413
#NineToey

617
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:55,463
I'm sure everyone has seen the pilot

618
00:34:55,463 --> 00:34:57,933
of "Engineering Mess" by now, right?

619
00:34:58,200 --> 00:35:00,533
"We got to work with a top-tier lead, too.
(Comment: Nine-Toey only)"

620
00:35:00,533 --> 00:35:01,200
"How do you feel?
(Comment: Nine-Toey onlyyy)"

621
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:05,100
"It's good. He's a very good co-worker.
(Comment: +1111)"

622
00:35:05,386 --> 00:35:06,466
Comment: If you don't open your mind,
it's just not the same.

623
00:35:06,466 --> 00:35:09,088
So, let's read some comments instead.

624
00:35:09,088 --> 00:35:13,366
"Let's see how the fans feel.
(Comment: Skipping this, I really can't.)"

625
00:35:13,366 --> 00:35:14,698
(Comment: The audience probably won't feel it.)

626
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,758
Uh, I think we should switch to talking about

627
00:35:20,758 --> 00:35:22,766
the behind-the-scenes stuff instead.

628
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:25,000
I think the fans would want to know a lot.

629
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:25,983
Sure, of course.

630
00:35:25,983 --> 00:35:26,817
Okay, okay.

631
00:35:31,919 --> 00:35:34,391
This won't go very far.

632
00:35:34,391 --> 00:35:36,391
Seeing this just makes me miss the old couple.

633
00:35:36,391 --> 00:35:38,391
Turning off the live, it's ruining the mood.

634
00:35:38,391 --> 00:35:40,000
Scrolling past this. Bye.

635
00:35:42,050 --> 00:35:43,963
The audience will definitely leave.

636
00:35:43,963 --> 00:35:45,963
Nine-Toey onlyyy!

637
00:35:49,966 --> 00:35:51,000
I'll be right back.

638
00:35:53,133 --> 00:35:54,466
Hang in there, Guy.

639
00:35:55,266 --> 00:35:56,066
Thank you.

640
00:36:02,733 --> 00:36:04,782
Hey, how was your day?

641
00:36:04,782 --> 00:36:06,804
Sorry I didn't get to watch your live.

642
00:36:06,804 --> 00:36:08,766
I was shooting commercials all day.

643
00:36:08,980 --> 00:36:09,480
It was good.

644
00:36:10,243 --> 00:36:11,810
Just finished the live.

645
00:36:12,166 --> 00:36:15,162
Oh, the crew really loved the teaser.

646
00:36:15,162 --> 00:36:16,966
Everyone's praising your acting.

647
00:36:17,966 --> 00:36:18,766
Really?

648
00:36:19,266 --> 00:36:19,933
Yeah.

649
00:36:19,933 --> 00:36:22,128
I think we should go back and celebrate.

650
00:36:22,128 --> 00:36:23,966
I'll buy lots of snacks for you.

651
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:26,066
Hey.

652
00:36:27,019 --> 00:36:28,200
When are you coming back?

653
00:36:29,333 --> 00:36:31,922
Mmm, I think I'll be there by evening.

654
00:36:31,922 --> 00:36:34,094
Because from here to Bangkok

655
00:36:34,094 --> 00:36:35,800
it's two hours, not counting traffic.

656
00:36:37,666 --> 00:36:38,900
Can you hurry back a bit?

657
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:42,133
Is something wrong?

658
00:36:44,466 --> 00:36:45,333
It's nothing.

659
00:36:46,466 --> 00:36:47,500
You should go back to work.

660
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,133
Drive safely.

661
00:36:50,366 --> 00:36:51,333
See you soon.

662
00:37:00,261 --> 00:37:01,608
Such a waste of a good novel.

663
00:37:01,608 --> 00:37:02,559
Toey is cuter.

664
00:37:02,559 --> 00:37:03,224
I wonder what the producer was thinking.

665
00:37:03,224 --> 00:37:04,318
Not watching.

666
00:37:04,318 --> 00:37:04,818
Is it too late for a recast?

667
00:37:04,818 --> 00:37:05,505
Nine didn't join the live, which means...

668
00:37:05,505 --> 00:37:06,172
deep down, Nine doesn't want to pair with Toey.

669
00:37:06,172 --> 00:37:06,672
That's why he didn't join.

670
00:37:06,672 --> 00:37:08,672
Think carefully, producer. Think again.

671
00:37:11,914 --> 00:37:14,508
"I've followed Tor Prakai for a long time,
since he was still doing Likay."

672
00:37:14,508 --> 00:37:17,605
"He's a country boy with no connections,
just pure effort."

673
00:37:17,605 --> 00:37:21,988
"And with his dedication, if Tor Prakai reads this,
I want to say that I'm always rooting for him."

674
00:37:21,988 --> 00:37:25,708
"No matter what Tor Prakai does, I will be his FC
No. 1 forever."

675
00:37:31,191 --> 00:37:34,100
(Incoming call from Ploy Ying)

676
00:37:39,333 --> 00:37:42,566
Guy, your series teaser looks so good!

677
00:37:43,266 --> 00:37:45,578
And your acting is great, too.

678
00:37:45,578 --> 00:37:47,566
You've really done Petchprakai house proud.

679
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,567
Uh, and those bad comments,

680
00:37:51,139 --> 00:37:52,520
don't pay any attention to them.

681
00:37:52,854 --> 00:37:55,806
They're just crazy "shipper" fans.

682
00:37:55,806 --> 00:37:58,600
I'm busy cussing them back right now.

683
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:00,133
It's okay, P'Ploy.

684
00:38:01,066 --> 00:38:02,400
It's just a difference of opinion.

685
00:38:02,933 --> 00:38:04,400
"Difference of opinion" my ass!

686
00:38:04,766 --> 00:38:06,933
I can see all the hateful messages right here.

687
00:38:07,666 --> 00:38:10,203
Even Pleng and Ping Pong Chae

688
00:38:10,203 --> 00:38:11,533
are helping you out, too.

689
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:12,866
Look over there.

690
00:38:15,066 --> 00:38:17,300
I don't want everyone to get upset over this.

691
00:38:17,900 --> 00:38:19,206
Not at all.

692
00:38:19,206 --> 00:38:22,016
But there's one person who's the angriest.

693
00:38:22,016 --> 00:38:22,718
Over there.

694
00:38:23,672 --> 00:38:24,767
It's Phet.

695
00:38:24,767 --> 00:38:26,973
Phet, say hello to the camera.

696
00:38:33,733 --> 00:38:35,300
That guy is the angriest.

697
00:38:35,766 --> 00:38:37,333
He's had that face since this morning.

698
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:40,100
Probably still thinking of ways to curse the antis.

699
00:38:40,700 --> 00:38:42,201
Fight on, Guy!

700
00:38:42,201 --> 00:38:44,659
We're going to ride around the whole district

701
00:38:44,659 --> 00:38:46,200
to get everyone to boost your views.

702
00:38:48,466 --> 00:38:50,300
Petchprakai never leaves anyone behind.

703
00:38:52,100 --> 00:38:52,900
Never!

704
00:38:53,100 --> 00:38:55,366
We're on Team Guy. Keep fighting!

705
00:38:57,566 --> 00:38:58,366
Thanks, guys.

706
00:38:59,066 --> 00:38:59,866
Bye-bye.

707
00:39:00,266 --> 00:39:01,066
Bye-bye.

708
00:39:19,300 --> 00:39:20,933
I'm sorry I'm late.

709
00:39:21,533 --> 00:39:22,733
I hurried as much as I could.

710
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:24,088
It's okay.

711
00:39:26,118 --> 00:39:27,252
About...

712
00:39:27,689 --> 00:39:28,394
I'm okay.

713
00:39:28,966 --> 00:39:29,766
Huh?

714
00:39:30,666 --> 00:39:31,466
Really.

715
00:39:33,766 --> 00:39:36,000
So, what did you buy?

716
00:39:36,866 --> 00:39:38,066
I'm hungry.

717
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:42,310
Thank you.

718
00:39:43,693 --> 00:39:46,616
Oh, everyone, I want to tell you that Guy

719
00:39:46,616 --> 00:39:49,158
read the novel three whole times.
(Comment: Nine, please review Toey.)

720
00:39:49,158 --> 00:39:51,975
"His preparation was spot on.
(Comment: So forced, was it the agency's order?)"

721
00:39:51,975 --> 00:39:53,315
"He's perfect with his lines.
(Comment: Oh, a dual live!)"

722
00:39:53,315 --> 00:39:54,766
You don't believe me, do you?

723
00:39:56,466 --> 00:39:57,266
Look.

724
00:39:57,966 --> 00:40:00,100
"How do you think I should say this part?
(Comment: Oh my god, he read it 3 times!)"

725
00:40:00,100 --> 00:40:01,280
(Comment: He's so attentive.)

726
00:40:01,866 --> 00:40:03,644
"You want me to pretend to be your boyfriend?
(Comment: It's like he's making excuses for him.)"

727
00:40:03,644 --> 00:40:04,466
And...

728
00:40:04,466 --> 00:40:05,400
(Comment: Happy for the author.)

729
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:06,900
You want me to pretend to be your boyfriend?

730
00:40:07,133 --> 00:40:07,966
That's not all.

731
00:40:08,733 --> 00:40:09,533
Look.

732
00:40:09,533 --> 00:40:10,333
There's another clip.

733
00:40:10,466 --> 00:40:12,733
Gosh, why did you film so much?

734
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:15,566
"I think after you finish speaking…
(Comment: Surprisingly cute.)"

735
00:40:15,866 --> 00:40:18,666
...we should lock eyes a bit longer before you enter.
(Comment: Secretly shipping this, I'm falling for Guy.)

736
00:40:19,366 --> 00:40:20,166
Look.
(Comment: I have a weakness for hardworking kids.)

737
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:22,533
"And when will Guy want to have Nine?
(Comment: Their chemistry is quite good.)"

738
00:40:22,533 --> 00:40:24,008
(Comment: Is this fanservice?)

739
00:40:24,008 --> 00:40:25,533
(Comment: #NineGuy)

740
00:40:25,533 --> 00:40:26,333
Let's eat.

741
00:40:26,533 --> 00:40:27,333
See?

742
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,800
For someone this dedicated,

743
00:40:29,566 --> 00:40:30,066
look.

744
00:40:30,066 --> 00:40:31,366
Everyone, look at his script.

745
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,000
"Hey, I'm going to keep this as a souvenir.
(Comment: A new chemistry, let's give it a try.)"

746
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:34,636
(Comment: Still don't quite like it.)

747
00:40:34,636 --> 00:40:35,136
(Comment: Where's the #NineGuy fandom entrance?)

748
00:40:35,136 --> 00:40:35,948
What a blessing for fans, such a dedicated actor.

749
00:40:35,948 --> 00:40:37,081
"He worked so hard on his homework.
(They use formal 'I' and 'You', but we're shipping it.)"

750
00:40:37,081 --> 00:40:37,962
"He worked so hard on his homework.
(Moments are here, teasing each other is cute.)"

751
00:40:38,392 --> 00:40:39,251
Give it here.

752
00:40:39,251 --> 00:40:39,751
No.

753
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:40,674
Give it to me.

754
00:40:40,674 --> 00:40:41,174
No.

755
00:40:41,508 --> 00:40:42,056
Give it!

756
00:40:42,056 --> 00:40:42,672
No.

757
00:40:43,673 --> 00:40:44,936
Give it here!

758
00:40:44,936 --> 00:40:45,617
No.

759
00:40:46,471 --> 00:40:46,995
Give it to me!

760
00:40:47,806 --> 00:40:48,974
Give it back to me.

761
00:40:52,333 --> 00:40:54,966
So, does this "brother-in-law" pass?

762
00:40:58,533 --> 00:40:59,533
He's not my brother-in-law.

763
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:05,349
P'Phet.

764
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:07,353
We've got a serious problem!

765
00:41:12,133 --> 00:41:14,200
Hey, the costumes are gone!

766
00:41:16,066 --> 00:41:16,800
What happened?

767
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:18,800
All of our Likay costumes are gone.

768
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,233
What? How could they just disappear?

769
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:23,566
Yeah, there were so many. How did they take them?

770
00:41:23,766 --> 00:41:24,466
I...

771
00:41:24,466 --> 00:41:26,266
asked Headman Mai for the CCTV footage,

772
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:27,766
and he's checking it right now.

773
00:41:27,966 --> 00:41:30,333
Is anything else missing besides the clothes?

774
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:34,666
The cameras and livestream gear you had me buy.

775
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:37,600
And the jewelry too.

776
00:41:38,333 --> 00:41:39,133
The jewelry.

777
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:46,964
I'm...

778
00:41:46,964 --> 00:41:47,994
so

779
00:41:47,994 --> 00:41:49,013
sorry,

780
00:42:39,100 --> 00:42:39,848
P'Phet.

781
00:42:39,848 --> 00:42:42,451
Dad and I checked the CCTV for the whole village.

782
00:42:42,451 --> 00:42:44,999
But strangely, we didn't find anything.

783
00:42:45,285 --> 00:42:48,557
I think the thieves haven't moved the stuff yet.

784
00:42:50,700 --> 00:42:52,733
So what can we do now?

785
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:02,666
Pleng, we told the followers we'd live today, right?

786
00:43:03,100 --> 00:43:04,533
We already ran the ads.

787
00:43:12,133 --> 00:43:13,766
I've thought of something good.

788
00:43:16,066 --> 00:43:17,400
Has everyone heard this saying?

789
00:43:18,266 --> 00:43:19,600
"The sword is in the heart."

790
00:43:20,333 --> 00:43:22,866
"Even a bamboo branch is invincible."

791
00:43:31,933 --> 00:43:34,854
Hello, this is the Petchprakai Troupe. Today,

792
00:43:34,854 --> 00:43:37,923
we've shed our Likay costumes for a rustic kitchen

793
00:43:37,923 --> 00:43:42,015
"to cook some delicious food
that Ayutthaya people eat often."

794
00:43:42,015 --> 00:43:45,866
Presented by our highly talented little chef.

795
00:43:47,500 --> 00:43:48,824
How did you think of this?

796
00:43:48,824 --> 00:43:51,688
Using phones to film ourselves and

797
00:43:51,688 --> 00:43:53,400
dressing casually like this.

798
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:57,441
Well, I saw that your seniors are already talented.

799
00:43:57,441 --> 00:43:59,663
Even without costumes or high production,

800
00:43:59,663 --> 00:44:02,066
they can still sing and dance, right?

801
00:44:02,333 --> 00:44:04,143
Plus, I think doing it this way

802
00:44:04,143 --> 00:44:07,300
makes it clearer how cool they really are.

803
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,766
Did the university teach you this?

804
00:44:12,333 --> 00:44:14,066
If you want to know, you have to study yourself.

805
00:44:14,466 --> 00:44:18,069
Okay, I'll definitely study hard then

806
00:44:18,069 --> 00:44:21,101
to develop Petchprakai even further.

807
00:44:21,101 --> 00:44:23,100
And I'll be even better than you, just watch.

808
00:44:23,466 --> 00:44:24,266
Hmph.

809
00:44:24,866 --> 00:44:25,366
Oh.

810
00:44:25,366 --> 00:44:26,366
That'll be a bit tough, dear.

811
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:28,266
I'll be waiting to see.

812
00:44:28,733 --> 00:44:29,533
Okay.

813
00:44:30,066 --> 00:44:31,133
It was all over my face just now.

814
00:44:33,066 --> 00:44:35,466
♪ The cook's skill ♪

815
00:44:36,515 --> 00:44:38,438
♪ is truly divine, ♪

816
00:44:38,438 --> 00:44:44,803
♪ with flavors so bold and fine. ♪

817
00:44:44,803 --> 00:44:49,605
♪ Treng treng treng ♪

818
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:56,100
Is everyone here?

819
00:44:56,333 --> 00:44:58,266
I want to have a meeting about the missing items.

820
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:00,400
Mmm.

821
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:02,766
Ping Pong Chae is missing.

822
00:45:03,800 --> 00:45:04,800
I don't know what he's doing.

823
00:45:04,933 --> 00:45:06,333
I saw him taking a shower a long time ago.

824
00:45:07,066 --> 00:45:07,784
But just now,

825
00:45:08,309 --> 00:45:10,066
I saw the bathroom was empty.

826
00:45:11,100 --> 00:45:11,600
Hey!

827
00:45:11,600 --> 00:45:12,766
Did he go out?

828
00:45:13,666 --> 00:45:14,666
I wasn't looking either.

829
00:45:14,866 --> 00:45:16,600
I was too busy tidying up.

830
00:45:16,933 --> 00:45:17,966
I'll call him myself.

831
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:25,331
The number you have dialed...

832
00:45:25,331 --> 00:45:30,152
...cannot be reached at this time.

833
00:45:31,058 --> 00:45:31,819
Can't get through.

834
00:45:35,566 --> 00:45:36,866
Try calling one more time.

835
00:45:42,266 --> 00:45:42,766
The number you have dialed...

836
00:45:42,766 --> 00:45:46,466
...cannot be reached at this time.

837
00:45:51,166 --> 00:45:52,242
No signal.

838
00:45:52,242 --> 00:45:52,742
Yeah.

839
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:53,800
It's not connecting.

840
00:45:55,566 --> 00:45:56,700
Call again.

841
00:45:58,266 --> 00:45:59,066
The number you have dialed...

842
00:45:59,066 --> 00:46:02,533
...cannot be reached at this time.

843
00:46:05,333 --> 00:46:06,333
I think this is suspicious.

844
00:46:06,500 --> 00:46:07,666
I'll go down and check on him.

845
00:46:09,133 --> 00:46:09,933
I'm coming too.

846
00:46:20,949 --> 00:46:22,515
Hey!

847
00:46:29,700 --> 00:46:30,500
Don't tell me...

848
00:46:31,733 --> 00:46:32,533
that...

849
00:46:33,066 --> 00:46:34,700
...he took the chance while we weren't looking...

850
00:46:34,800 --> 00:46:35,733
...and ran away.

851
00:46:37,666 --> 00:46:38,766
Why would he do that?

852
00:46:42,466 --> 00:46:43,566
Hey, be careful.

853
00:46:44,733 --> 00:46:46,100
Come, walk slowly.

854
00:46:50,666 --> 00:46:52,066
Are you okay?

855
00:46:53,366 --> 00:46:54,166
I'm fine.

856
00:46:57,366 --> 00:46:59,566
It's okay, I'll pick it up myself.

857
00:47:00,166 --> 00:47:00,966
I'm sorry.

858
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:02,369
Did something happen?

859
00:47:02,607 --> 00:47:03,350
Why

860
00:47:03,732 --> 00:47:05,133
are you spacing out like this?

861
00:47:05,966 --> 00:47:08,200
The feedback from the live was good.

862
00:47:12,066 --> 00:47:12,866
All of a sudden,

863
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:16,766
I just started thinking about P'Phet.

864
00:47:18,733 --> 00:47:19,933
When you told me

865
00:47:20,166 --> 00:47:21,766
that I worked hard on the script,

866
00:47:22,566 --> 00:47:24,000
I actually learned that from him.

867
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:28,000
He taught me acting

868
00:47:29,400 --> 00:47:31,300
and to respect the original work.

869
00:47:33,533 --> 00:47:34,600
I want to see him.

870
00:47:35,733 --> 00:47:36,766
And thank him.

871
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:41,288
Then how about this?

872
00:47:41,288 --> 00:47:42,367
Whenever we're free,

873
00:47:42,367 --> 00:47:44,212
let's go see him together.

874
00:47:44,212 --> 00:47:48,000
"I'm sure your brother misses you a lot too,
just the same."

875
00:48:01,500 --> 00:48:03,000
Could it be those three?

876
00:48:04,366 --> 00:48:06,866
Have they been acting strange lately?

877
00:48:08,066 --> 00:48:10,208
I'm not really sure, Headman Mai.

878
00:48:10,208 --> 00:48:12,980
But I noticed that they...

879
00:48:12,980 --> 00:48:15,357
...are really addicted to their phones lately.

880
00:48:15,357 --> 00:48:17,933
Like, even more than I am.

881
00:48:43,100 --> 00:48:53,000
♪ No matter how heavy the burden, it shall pass one day. ♪

882
00:48:55,200 --> 00:49:00,000
♪ We shall remain to fight the fray. ♪

883
00:49:01,355 --> 00:49:07,154
♪ With you and me by each other's side. ♪

884
00:49:08,394 --> 00:49:10,891
♪ Though the troubles ♪

885
00:49:11,321 --> 00:49:13,940
♪ come flooding in like the tide, ♪

886
00:49:15,104 --> 00:49:18,715
♪ there's still someone ♪

887
00:49:19,383 --> 00:49:22,454
♪ to understand and guide. ♪

888
00:49:28,466 --> 00:49:31,700
Our expenses are way more than we earn.

889
00:49:32,071 --> 00:49:34,871
Maybe Por Tor can help us.

890
00:49:35,666 --> 00:49:37,682
Of course. If it's for the Petchprakai Troupe,

891
00:49:37,682 --> 00:49:39,166
I'm more than happy to help.

892
00:49:41,100 --> 00:49:42,270
From now on,

893
00:49:42,270 --> 00:49:45,200
our Petchprakai Troupe must be a professional team.

894
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:47,320
It's not like a home anymore.

895
00:49:47,320 --> 00:49:49,333
It's more like a company that has to hit targets.

896
00:49:49,566 --> 00:49:51,613
For the job Por Tor just took, he got 350,000.

897
00:49:51,613 --> 00:49:53,900
But why did he tell P'Phet it was only 300,000?

898
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,066
Por Tor might not actually be cheating us.

899
00:49:56,500 --> 00:49:57,866
I love this place like a home.

900
00:49:58,066 --> 00:49:59,900
But if living here means nobody trusts each other,

901
00:50:00,166 --> 00:50:01,400
it's just not home anymore.
